  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA294-kiḷavi">itu maṇamaṉaiyuṭ pukka tōḻi talaimakaḷatu kaviṉkaṇṭu colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said who entered the marriage house upon seeing HER beauty.</p>
        </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA294">
<l>            tīyum vaḷiyum vicumpupayan tāṅku</l>
<l>            nōyu miṉpamu mākiṉṟu mātō</l>
<l>            māya maṉṟu tōḻi vēypayiṉ</l>
<l>            ṟeruvai nīṭiya peruvarai yakantoṟun</l>
<l>            toṉṟuṟai tuppoṭu muraṇmikac ciṉaiik </l>
<l>            koṉṟa yāṉaik kōṭukaṇ ṭaṉṉa</l>
<l>            cempuṭaik koḻumukai yaviḻnta kāntaḷ</l>
<l>            cilampuṭaṉ kamaḻuñ cāra</l>
<l>            lilaṅkumalai nāṭaṉ malarnta mārpē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent2">As the sky’s spreading fire and wind,</l>
<l>hasn’t it become pain and pleasure?</l>
<l>– the blooming chest of the man from a land of shining mountains</l>
<l rend="indent3">with slopes, where the Malabar-lily that opened [its] rich buds</l>
<l rend="indent3">with red sides spreads fragrance all along the mountain slopes,</l>
<l rend="indent2">as if seeing the tusks of an elephant that has killed,</l>
<l rend="indent4">in an uprise of long-established bitter antagonism,<note place="foot">For an almost complete formulaic parallel line see NA 247.1 + note.</note></l>
<l rend="indent">in every inside of the great mountains where the reeds have grown</l>
<l rend="indent">long [and] the bamboo rustled.</l>
<l rend="indent4">It is no illusion, friend.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
